// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0
// Copyright 2026 Schuberg Philis
//
// compiler/parser.mvl — S3: recursive-descent MVL parser (issue #187)
//
// Parses a flat List[Token] (from compiler/lexer.mvl) into a Program AST
// (compiler/tir.mvl).  Handles all top-level declaration kinds:
//   use, const, type, fn (with modifiers), extern, impl,
//   actor, effect, label, relabel
//
// Design:
//   - ParserState threads { tokens, pos, errors } through every parse fn.
//   - Result carriers (BoolR, StringR, …) carry (value, updated_state) because
//     MVL has no tuple syntax and no generic user types.
//   - partial fn throughout (while-loops, self-recursion in type parser).
//   - Type expression parsing uses a depth counter to avoid mutual recursion:
//     parse_type_expr_depth(ps, 4) recurses via itself with depth-1, so no
//     forward declaration is needed.
//   - IFC bridge: transparent partial fn call_parse(src) → Program.
//
// Termination argument (Req 8):
//   Two patterns cover every loop and recursive call in this file:
//
//   1. Token-position loops — any while loop with !ps_at_eof(curr) in the guard:
//      Every branch either advances curr via ps_advance (pos += 1) or sets a
//      boolean flag that exits the loop.  The token list is finite and immutable,
//      so curr.pos reaches tokens.len() in at most O(n) steps.
//      Formal measure:  curr.tokens.len() - curr.pos
//      Written as:      decreases curr.tokens.len() - curr.pos
//      (#726: len() now accepts field-access arguments)
//
//   2. Depth-bounded recursion — parse_type_expr_depth(ps, max_depth):
//      Every recursive call passes max_depth - 1.  The requires max_depth >= 0
//      contract (proven at Req 10) ensures the base case is reached.
//      No while loop in this function can increase max_depth, so both the
//      recursion and its inner loops terminate.
//
// Public surface: parse(tokens: List[Token]) -> Program

